ðŸ”¬This is a nightly-only experimental API. (`io_slice_advance`Â [#62726](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/62726))

Advance a slice of slices.

Shrinks the slice to remove any `IoSliceMut`s that are fully advanced over. If the cursor ends up in the middle of an `IoSliceMut`, it is modified to start at that cursor.

For example, if we have a slice of two 8-byte `IoSliceMut`s, and we advance by 10 bytes, the result will only include the second `IoSliceMut`, advanced by 2 bytes.

##### [Â§](#panics-2)Panics

Panics when trying to advance beyond the end of the slices.

##### [Â§](#examples-1)Examples

```
#![feature(io_slice_advance)]

use std::io::IoSliceMut;
use std::ops::Deref;

let mut buf1 = [1; 8];
let mut buf2 = [2; 16];
let mut buf3 = [3; 8];
let mut bufs = &mut [
    IoSliceMut::new(&mut buf1),
    IoSliceMut::new(&mut buf2),
    IoSliceMut::new(&mut buf3),
][..];

// Mark 10 bytes as read.
IoSliceMut::advance_slices(&mut bufs, 10);
assert_eq!(bufs[0].deref(), [2; 14].as_ref());
assert_eq!(bufs[1].deref(), [3; 8].as_ref());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0A%23!%5Bfeature(io_slice_advance)%5D%0A%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::io::IoSliceMut;%0A++++use+std::ops::Deref;%0A++++%0A++++let+mut+buf1+=+%5B1;+8%5D;%0A++++let+mut+buf2+=+%5B2;+16%5D;%0A++++let+mut+buf3+=+%5B3;+8%5D;%0A++++let+mut+bufs+=+%26mut+%5B%0A++++++++IoSliceMut::new(%26mut+buf1),%0A++++++++IoSliceMut::new(%26mut+buf2),%0A++++++++IoSliceMut::new(%26mut+buf3),%0A++++%5D%5B..%5D;%0A++++%0A++++//+Mark+10+bytes+as+read.%0A++++IoSliceMut::advance_slices(%26mut+bufs,+10);%0A++++assert_eq!(bufs%5B0%5D.deref(),+%5B2;+14%5D.as_ref());%0A++++assert_eq!(bufs%5B1%5D.deref(),+%5B3;+8%5D.as_ref());%0A%7D&version=nightly&edition=2021)

