1.0.0 Â· [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/slice/mod.rs.html#762)

Returns a raw pointer to the sliceâ€™s buffer.

The caller must ensure that the slice outlives the pointer this function returns, or else it will end up pointing to garbage.

The caller must also ensure that the memory the pointer (non-transitively) points to is never written to (except inside an `UnsafeCell`) using this pointer or any pointer derived from it. If you need to mutate the contents of the slice, use [`as_mut_ptr`](about:blank/primitive.slice.html#method.as_mut_ptr "method slice::as_mut_ptr").

Modifying the container referenced by this slice may cause its buffer to be reallocated, which would also make any pointers to it invalid.

##### [Â§](#examples-28)Examples

```
let x = &[1, 2, 4];
let x_ptr = x.as_ptr();

unsafe {
    for i in 0..x.len() {
        assert_eq!(x.get_unchecked(i), &*x_ptr.add(i));
    }
}
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++let+x+=+%26%5B1,+2,+4%5D;%0A++++let+x_ptr+=+x.as_ptr();%0A++++%0A++++unsafe+%7B%0A++++++++for+i+in+0..x.len()+%7B%0A++++++++++++assert_eq!(x.get_unchecked(i),+%26*x_ptr.add(i));%0A++++++++%7D%0A++++%7D%0A%7D&edition=2021)

